    <id>tag:dexpairs.xyz,2021-08-10:welcome-nfts</id>
    <!--<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://dexpairs.xyz/news?title=welcome-nfts"/>-->
    <title>Welcome NFTs !</title>
    <published>2021-08-10T01:00:00Z</published>
    <updated>2021-08-10T01:00:00Z</updated>
    <content type="xhtml">
      <div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
        <h2 class="chapter-title">Explore ERC-721 transactions</h2>
        <div class="content">
          <p>
            <a href="https://dexpairs.xyz/wallet">The Wallet tracker</a> can now explore ERC-721 transactions in order to find tokens.<br />
            ERC-721 tokens are also well known as ... NFTs !<br />
            Yes, your <a href="https://ethereum.org/en/nft/" target="_blank" rel="external">Non-Fungible Tokens</a> are now displayed in the wallet !
          </p>
        </div>
        <h2 class="chapter-title">How can I view my NFTs ?</h2>
        <div class="content">
          <p>
            To view a NFT, the contract has to respect the <a href="https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-721" target="_blank" rel="external">ERC-721 standard</a> and must implement the optionnal <i>tokenURI</i> function. Just sit in your chair and let the Wallet search this for you !<br />
            Otherwise, use the contract address to find where to preview the NFT.
          </p>
        </div>
